    item-15 at level 2: picture
      item-15 at level 3: caption: Fig. 1. Types of hotspots. (A) summarizes the characteristics of non-PRDM9 recombination hotspots: i. recombination machinery does not recognize specific sequences to initiate recombination; ii. recombination takes place in promoter regions; iii. the rate of recombination remains constant over time (self-preserving hotspots); iv. the location of hotspots in the genome does not change over evolutionary time. (B) summarizes the characteristics of PRDM9 recombination hotspots: i. PRDM9 recognizes and binds specific sequences recruiting the recombination machinery to initiate recombination in those sequences; ii. recombination takes place in nonfunctional genomic regions; iii. the rate of recombination decreases over time (self-destructive hotspots); iv. the location of hotspots changes rapidly over evolutionary time.
